=Description=

"The online forum for disseminating knowledge about community and complementary currencies around the world.

These new systems of exchange aim to:

•promote local economic development,
   
•build social capital,
   
•nurture more sustainable lifestyles and
   
•meet needs which mainstream money does not.

From green money and 'solidarity' exchange to business barter networks, and covering historical and contemporary initiatives, the journal bridges the divide between academics and activists to promote mutual understanding and learning from good practice."
(http://www.ijccr.net/IJCCR/IJCCR_Home.html)


